# process so format aligns with given example
df1 = df[['StudentTestID','StudentGradeLevel','eperf2', 'mperf2', 'sperf2']] 
df2 = df[['StudentTestID','StudentGradeLevel','escaleds', 'mscaleds', 'sscaleds']]
df3 = df[['StudentTestID','StudentGradeLevel', 'ecpi','mcpi','scpi']]
df4 = df1.melt(id_vars=['StudentTestID','StudentGradeLevel'], value_name="Score1Value")
values = {'eperf2':'April 1', 'mperf2':'May 1', 'sperf2':'June 1'}
df4["TestDate"] = [values[j] for i in df4["variable"] for j in values if j==i]
values = {'eperf2':'MCAS ELA', 'mperf2':'MCAS Math', 'sperf2':'MCAS Science'}
df4["TestTypeName"] = [values[j] for i in df4["variable"] for j in values if j==i]
values = {'eperf2':'ELA', 'mperf2':'Math', 'sperf2':'Science'}
df4["TestSubjectName"] = [values[j] for i in df4["variable"] for j in values if j==i]
dict = {'value':'Score1Value'}
df4.rename(columns=dict, inplace=True)
df4['TestGradeLevel'] = df4['StudentGradeLevel']
df4['NCESID'] = 373737
df4['StudentLocalID'] = 'missing'
df4['TestName'] = 'MCAS'
df4['Score1Label'] = 'Performance Level'
df4['Score1Type'] = 'Level'
del df4['variable']
df4.loc[df4["Score1Value"] == "F","Score1Value"] = "1-F"
df4.loc[df4["Score1Value"] == "W","Score1Value"] = "2-W"
df4.loc[df4["Score1Value"] == "NI","Score1Value"] = "3-NI"
df4.loc[df4["Score1Value"] == "P","Score1Value"] = "4-P"
df4.loc[df4["Score1Value"] == "A","Score1Value"] = "5-A"
df4.loc[df4["Score1Value"] == "P+","Score1Value"] = "6-P+"
df4.sort_values(by="StudentTestID", inplace=True)
df5 = df2.melt(id_vars=['StudentTestID','StudentGradeLevel'], value_name="Score2Value")
values = {'escaleds':'April 1', 'mscaleds':'May 1', 'sscaleds':'June 1'}
df5["TestDate"] = [values[j] for i in df5["variable"] for j in values if j==i]
values = {'escaleds':'MCAS ELA', 'mscaleds':'MCAS Math', 'sscaleds':'MCAS Science'}
df5["TestTypeName"] = [values[j] for i in df5["variable"] for j in values if j==i]
values = {'escaleds':'ELA', 'mscaleds':'Math', 'sscaleds':'Science'}
df5["TestSubjectName"] = [values[j] for i in df5["variable"] for j in values if j==i]
dict = {'value':'Score2Value'}
df5.rename(columns=dict, inplace=True)
df5['TestGradeLevel'] = df5['StudentGradeLevel']
df5['NCESID'] = 373737
df5['TestName'] = 'MCAS'
df5['StudentLocalID'] = 'missing'
df5['Score2Label'] = 'Scaled Score'
df5['Score2Type'] = 'Scale'
del df5['variable']
df5.sort_values(by="StudentTestID", inplace=True)
df6 = df3.melt(id_vars=['StudentTestID','StudentGradeLevel'], value_name="Score3Value")
values = {'ecpi':'April 1', 'mcpi':'May 1', 'scpi':'June 1'}
df6["TestDate"] = [values[j] for i in df6["variable"] for j in values if j==i]
values = {'ecpi':'MCAS ELA', 'mcpi':'MCAS Math', 'scpi':'MCAS Science'}
df6["TestTypeName"] = [values[j] for i in df6["variable"] for j in values if j==i]
values = {'ecpi':'ELA', 'mcpi':'Math', 'scpi':'Science'}
df6["TestSubjectName"] = [values[j] for i in df6["variable"] for j in values if j==i]
dict = {'value':'Score3Value'}
df6.rename(columns=dict, inplace=True)
df6['TestGradeLevel'] = df6['StudentGradeLevel']
df6['NCESID'] = 373737
df6['TestName'] = 'MCAS'
df6['StudentLocalID'] = 'missing'

edf = df6.merge(df7,on=["StudentTestID","TestDate","TestTypeName","TestSubjectName","TestGradeLevel","NCESID","StudentLocalID","TestName","StudentGradeLevel"])

# download final output as .csv
import base64
from IPython.display import HTML

def create_download_link( edf, title = "Download CSV file", filename = "edf.csv"):
    csv = edf.to_csv()
    b64 = base64.b64encode(csv.encode())
    payload = b64.decode()
    html = '<a download="{filename}" href="data:text/csv;base64,{payload}" target="_blank">{title}</a>'
    html = html.format(payload=payload,title=title,filename=filename)
    return HTML(html)

edf = pd.DataFrame(edf)
create_download_link(edf)
